main event: A radar observed an unidentified object that appeared as a first magnitude star, moving erratically at an elevation of 38,000 degrees and an azimuth of 250 degrees.
interesting points: The object pulsated intermittently and had bright flashes observed during the sighting.
The observation lasted for 38 minutes, with the object moving on an erratic course.
The radar could not determine if the object was a satellite, as it did not echo on the radar scope during the observation.
The sighting occurred on September 13, 1962 at the coordinates 31.19N, 163.03E.
There were two witnesses to the event, but no photographs were included in the report.
sighted object: an unidentified object that appeared as a first magnitude star
